Dear Diary;

Today I saw a Contact after spending twelve hours walking through the jungle. Someone else shot him, but, it was fun anyway.

10/10

Well, played only the campaign, spent 27 hours on it and I can tell you that this game may be a modern warfare simulator, but it's very clumsy and unpolished in one way. I enjoy the realism of this game very much:
1. it really makes you think what you do and face your consequences if you do some stupid stuff, the game requires strategic thinking (unlike such arcades as cod or battlefield in singleplayer modes);
2. the enviroment is also amazing, realistic - putting you in charge of choosing what wall or tree will be your life saver;
3. overall, it look pretty good, not perfect, but enjoyable.
BUT there are flaws that just make you think that first graders produced this game:
1. the AI has the worst algorithms in this game, it's clumsy appearance balances off all the realism;
2. the AI difficulty as in all games in singleplayer mode is off, unrealistic;
3. the amount of work to be done by YOU during a mission sometimes (e.g. when you have to control  a squad, when you have to use new equipment (which makes you fail a mission 9 times before you learn how to use it and finally complete the mission)) is just way too much and the whole war feel during a mission goes down - this balances off the realism, which has been put in the enviroment so qualitatively.

So, 5/10, don't buy it unless you want to play it in multiplayer mode.
